            <div style="text-align: center; font-weight: bold; color:
              rgb(0, 0, 238);"><font face="Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif"><big>THE














                  WHY, WHAT, AND WHO OF THIS WEBSITE</big><br>
              </font> </div>
            <font face="Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif"> </font>
            <div style="text-align: justify;"><small style="font-family:
                arial; font-weight: bold;"><br>
              </small>
              <div style="text-align: justify;"><small
                  style="font-family: arial; font-weight: bold;"><span
                    style="color: rgb(0, 0, 153);"></span></small><font
                  size="-1" face="Arial" color="#000099"><b>Although
                    there are scores of websites that purport to
                    characterize the Jews and their impact on the world,
                    nearly all of them are sponsored by groups whose
                    ultimate objectives vis-à-vis the Jews and the State
                    of Israel range from defamation to outright
                    elimination.&nbsp; Many of the classic works of the
                    anti-Semitic canon, once confined to the fever
                    swamps, have become widely available via the
                    Internet.&nbsp; To this has been added a vast body
                    of anti-Zionist propaganda that frequently traffics
                    in anti-Semitic tropes and eliminationist
                    rhetoric.&nbsp; The purpose of this website is to
                    provide an online resource that <u><i>accurately</i></u>
                    describes the Jewish contribution to the cultural,
                    scientific, and technological evolution of
                    civilization.<br>
                    <br>
                  </b></font> </div>
              <small style="font-family: arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 153);
                font-weight: bold;"> <span style="color: rgb(0, 0,
                  238);"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 238);"><span
                      style="color: rgb(0, 0, 153);"></span></span></span></small><small
                style="font-family: arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 153);
                font-weight: bold;"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 238);"><span
                    style="color: rgb(0, 0, 238);"></span></span></small><font
                size="-1" face="Arial"><b>This contribution is
                  multifaceted and includes Monotheism, the Bible,
                  Judaism and Christianity, and thereby the moral
                  foundations of Western civilization; the concept of
                  linear (vs. cyclical) time, from which follows the
                  possibilities of freedom, progress, and hope; medical
                  advances that have saved the lives of more than 1.5
                  billion people; the Haber process, without which forty
                  percent of the world’s population could not be fed;
                  much of twentieth century physics, and thereby much of
                  the scientific basis of the physical-layer technology
                  underpinning the third and fourth industrial
                  revolutions; the work of 200+ Nobel Prize winners
                  (which absent the Holocaust and widespread <i>numerus</i>
                  <i>clausus</i> restrictions on access to higher
                  education and employment, would likely have been 300+
                  Nobel Prize winners); the $120 trillion international
                  bond market; the Broadway musical; the American film
                  industry; and the invention or co-invention of the
                  radio antenna, nuclear power, the transistor, the
                  laser, holography, the atomic clock, NMR spectroscopy
                  (the basis of MRI), antibiotics, chemotherapy,
                  monoclonal antibodies, genetic engineering, the
                  artificial heart valve, the heart pacemaker and
                  defibrillator, cybernetics, the von Neumann computer
                  architecture, the computer spreadsheet, the word
                  processor, BASIC, COBOL, Ada, LISP, linear
                  programming, public-key cryptography, blockchain,
                  artificial intelligence, quantum computing, cellular
                  telephony, the Internet, Google, and ChatGPT, to name
                  but a few.<br>
                  <br>
                </b></font><font size="-1" face="Arial"><b>JINFO.ORG has
                  no outside organizational affiliation or
                  sponsorship.&nbsp; Statistical metrics are extensively
                  employed because they are the most efficient technique
                  for objectively summarizing and conveying an overall
                  view of the large quantities of data involved.
                  Concerning Jewish identity, the vast majority (over
                  90%) of the individuals listed here as being Jewish
                  are such by virtue of having had two Jewish
                  parents.&nbsp; Also included, however, are individuals
                  with one Jewish parent, as well as a number of
                  Jews-by-choice, with the listings of individuals in
                  the latter two categories qualified as such.&nbsp; In
                  adopting this criterion for inclusion, we have largely
                  followed the practice employed by the Jewish
                  encyclopedias for more than a century. <br>
                  <br>
                </b></font>
